  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Multicenter randomized controlled trial (RCT) testing the effect of a dialogue-based
      psychosocial intervention for stroke acute survivors in primary care one to six months
      poststroke. Primary outcome is psycho-social health and wellbeing, measured by GHQ28 (primary
      outcome) and SAQoL (secondary outcome). 400 stroke survivors are randomized into intervention
      group or control group. Patients are followed up for 12 months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
